### <a  name="Hamblin" id="Hamblin"> </a>Vincent Corrigan and Vicki Hamblin

Music and Performance in Three French Hagiographic Mystery Plays   *METh 35* (2013) 95-139.

While it has rarely been the object of scholarly research, music was an integral part of French mystery plays of the late medieval era. This study focuses on three similarly-constructed French hagiographic plays to compare and contrast their instrumental, vocal and diabolic musical components. In both the *Mystery of
Saint Martin* by André de La Vigne and the *Jeu de saint
Estienne pape et martire* by Nicolas Loupvent, music not only accompanied but contributed to the narrative and to the pacing of the performance. *The Mystery of Saint Lawrence*, however, focuses only minimal attention to its music.

